SIMPLE: precentor
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Precentor
<hw>Pre*cen"tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>praecentor</ets>, fr. <ets>praecinere</ets> to sing before;
<ets>prae</ets> before + <ets>canere</ets> to sing. See
<er>Chant</er>.]</ety> <def>A leader of a choir; a directing
singer.</def> Specifically: <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The leader of the choir in
a cathedral; -- called also the <altname>chanter</altname> or
<xex>master</xex> of the choir.</def> <au>Hook.</au> <sd>(b)</sd>
<def>The leader of the congregational singing in Scottish and other
churches.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Precentorship</ent>⟦br⟧
